title: Regular Expressions in Tasker
message:
Regular Expressions in Tasker

Regex only via Tasker, no regex for builtin commands or tasks assigned
through Commandr.
Matched regex groups are transfered to Tasker as variables %commander_N
(where N is the group number)
Translations need to be updated accordingly.

title: Merge pull request #38 from emansih/master
message:
Merge pull request #38 from emansih/master

Awesome, thanks for contributing! I plan on rewriting the UI eventually, but it is not a huge priority at the moment as most ppl will setup Commandr once and then not return to the app. The Xposed toggle turns on Commandr's integration with Xposed, not the actual xposed module. This is necessary so that the accessibility service and xposed module do not conflict. In case you were wondering the planned UI will look something like Switchr's UI (swipeable list with different types of settings on different pages)... https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=mohammad.adib.switchr&hl=en  I also want to wait until Android L is released so I can redesign all at once.
